Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.14,0:00:04.52,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Together with the Detective Boys, Ran and company,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.52,0:00:07.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I boarded the Bell Tree Express.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.23,0:00:12.28,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suspicious passengers gathered in Carriage 8...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.90,0:00:16.37,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then, the deduction quiz taking place aboard the train
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.37,0:00:20.37,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}unexpectedly turned into a locked room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.25,0:00:26.00,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Meanwhile, the black shadow of the Organization
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:28.80,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}continued to close in on Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.30,0:00:34.51,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers,\Nhe solves every mystery and code!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.51,0:00:36.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A suspicious person and a bizarre trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.60,0:00:38.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Fate closes in on the unstoppable train!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.68,0:00:39.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.93,0:00:42.35,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.35,0:00:44.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.58,0:02:33.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fire from five years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.17,0:02:37.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do I have to do with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.17,0:02:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't bother playing dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just checked with the Shizuoka Police, who handled the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your name was on the list of survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.93,0:02:54.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, former Self-Defence Force member and sparring partner of the dead magnate, Taisaku Noto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.15,0:03:02.28,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Taisaku Noto (52)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room A
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.36,0:02:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got this scar on my cheek\Nfrom that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.19,0:03:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like I was hiding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.24,0:03:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.87,0:03:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you were carrying something on your shoulder when we first met, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tools for the locked room trick are in there, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.04,0:03:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was just my {\i1}shinai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.79,0:03:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shinai{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, just {\i1}shinai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.30,0:03:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I promised I'd spar with a friend in Nagoya when I get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.72,0:03:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if you don't need anything else—{***}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.81,0:03:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.89,0:03:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind running along the corridor for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:34.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Run?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might've seen the killer running away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.57,0:03:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So could I record a video of you running, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.74,0:03:51.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm the same Andō who was rescued from that fire along with Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.87,0:03:51.46,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Satoru Andō (41)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room C
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.87,0:03:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would've told you earlier had you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.92,0:03:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what's that big black bag in your room?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.17,0:04:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a painting I was asked to analyse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.38,0:04:05.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately, it turned out to be a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind if we took a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.97,0:04:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.81,0:04:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's pretty heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.73,0:04:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The forgery is solid gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.02,0:04:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Solid gold, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what was your relationship with the magnate?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.49,0:04:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The magnate was a famous art collector, and he used to show me his wide range of paintings,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.25,0:04:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,though almost all of them burnt up in the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.13,0:04:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must be pretty strong for an old man to carry something so heavy all on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.72,0:04:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then could you try running down the corridor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.93,0:04:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, I'll never be able to forget that fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.64,0:05:01.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to that fire that I now depend on this wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.06,0:05:01.11,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Natsue Komino (75)\NCarriage 8, Room D
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.06,0:05:01.11,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hiruka Sumitomo (37)\NCarriage 8, Room D
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.69,0:05:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you injured your legs in the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.61,0:05:05.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.45,0:05:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I won't be running down the corridor like the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.74,0:05:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your maid, Sumitomo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, can run, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I just have to run?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.09,0:05:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just run normally.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.05,0:05:29.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't see how you're gonna figure out who the killer is from this...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.14,0:05:32.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.89,0:05:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your maid's quite fast when she runs. Has she ever played sports?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.19,0:05:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, answer me, granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.20,0:05:57.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mari Idenami (33)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room E
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was the fiancée of the dead magnate's grandson,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.83,0:05:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and yes, I was rescued from the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but why do I have to show you how I run down a corridor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.13,0:06:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's just to check something...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, could you remove the chain-lock and let us in?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.55,0:06:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to come in, bring a search warrant!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.81,0:06:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's insane...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.47,0:06:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, about that wristwatch you found in your room... Has it rung again since?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.52,0:06:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wristwatch?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.57,0:06:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you can see, I left it out, but it hasn't rung again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.03,0:06:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, over there on the sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.66,0:06:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't see it through the gap...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:38.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.21,0:06:43.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When we found Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s corpse, I could see it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.75,0:06:48.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Through the gap in the door, I could see a bullet mark on the sofa opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.72,0:07:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we even got Idenami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to run down the corridor in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.40,0:07:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is there any actual meaning behind this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's show the videos we recorded to the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.73,0:07:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.07,0:07:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid, you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.74,0:07:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.75,0:08:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.25,0:08:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:11.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't changed a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.13,0:08:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.89,0:08:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Shū{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-nii{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.15,0:08:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shū{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-nii{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.32,0:08:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it really you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how? I thought you were dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.74,0:08:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the answer I wanted to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.54,0:08:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.29,0:08:44.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.71,0:08:46.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister's just a little anemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.88,0:08:48.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.24,0:09:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.16,0:09:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calling us out into the corridor like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.62,0:09:17.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you figure out anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.79,0:09:20.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, the investigation's still in the works...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.09,0:09:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that boy brought us from our rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.97,0:09:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said Sleeping Kogorō's deduction show was starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.55,0:09:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Uncle Kogorō, weren't you saying earlier that you knew how the plot went?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.39,0:09:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was metaphorical, you moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.78,0:09:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! It's Sleeping Kogorō!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.78,0:09:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s in that pose, then he solved the case, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.16,0:10:00.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You figured out the truth behind the murder in this first-class carriage's locked Room B.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.09,0:10:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.71,0:10:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry for not introducing myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.84,0:10:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s number one apprentice, Amuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.64,0:10:12.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.85,0:10:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I even checked the toilets in the other carriages nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.65,0:10:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an e-mail from Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.61,0:10:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm fine, so don't worry about me."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.53,0:10:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That {\i1}is{\i0} Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s e-mail address...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.82,0:10:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she's with Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.45,0:10:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's gotta be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wish we were there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.33,0:10:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't you just get up and go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.80,0:10:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the locked room murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.67,0:10:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I solved that mystery the second time I went to Idenami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s Room E.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.72,0:10:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, what? Are you saying {\i1}I'm{\i0} the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.02,0:11:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realized it when I looked into your room past the chain-locked door.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.19,0:11:08.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the chain lock on, no matter how much you try, there was one sofa you could hardly see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.40,0:11:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when Conan found Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body in Room B,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.91,0:11:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he could clearly see the right-hand sofa, even with the chain lock on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.29,0:11:23.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the kid misremembered?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.13,0:11:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason for that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.38,0:11:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was likely that there was one extra link in the chain lock, compared to the other rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.01,0:11:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gap would be wider,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.34,0:11:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and you'd be able to see more of the room from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.60,0:11:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.48,0:11:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a big problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.39,0:11:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A chain lock is normally set to a length that just barely keeps people from disengaging it even if they fit their hand in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.99,0:11:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So by adding an extra link, it makes it possible to lock the door from the outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.17,0:12:03.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.50,0:12:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't go around checking the passenger list!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.17,0:12:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.59,0:12:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd seen an old acquaintance on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.13,0:12:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it happens again, then please call for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.43,0:12:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.56,0:12:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right, there are six!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.65,0:12:31.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's five links in the other rooms' chains, but Room B has six!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.24,0:12:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is no longer a locked-room mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.07,0:12:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if somebody was loitering around the door, wouldn't the conductor notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.99,0:12:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.54,0:12:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he said he was in the corridor the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.21,0:12:47.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there {\i1}was{\i0} some stranger peering past a door at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.92,0:12:49.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.38,0:12:52.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't make them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.76,0:12:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd just gone into a tunnel, so it was very dim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.47,0:12:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it was probably the murderer, who then escaped into a different carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.14,0:13:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}could{\i0} be an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.52,0:13:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody in our carriage would carry out a crime
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.85,0:13:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with the risk of being recognized by a conductor who knows all of us waiting in the passageway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.94,0:13:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what if that risk could be removed with this little sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.49,0:13:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the room bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.83,0:13:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who rang it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.58,0:13:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.08,0:13:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just went into Room B, rang the bell, recorded the sound on my phone, and played it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.13,0:13:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Conductor, you heard the noise but didn't see a light come from any of the rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.42,0:13:35.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you went to Room A, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.97,0:13:37.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.05,0:13:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lightbulb above Room A had stopped working, so I thought it must be Noto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} calling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.64,0:13:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So while Noto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the conductor were arguing in doorway to Room A,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.27,0:13:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in Room B opened his door, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.82,0:13:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.40,0:13:54.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was on the phone with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.57,0:14:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So that was the moment when the killer went into Room B.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.07,0:14:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The corridors on this train are narrow enough that opening a door blocks most of the passageway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.20,0:14:07.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Room B's door was open,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.33,0:14:13.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the conductor in front of Room A wouldn't be able to see the killer coming from the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.13,0:14:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.47,0:14:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer probably called Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and said
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.55,0:14:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"There's some kind of disturbance outside the room. Has something happened?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.39,0:14:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, this happened as we were going through the tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.43,0:14:29.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer called Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} just before we entered the tunnel,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.77,0:14:32.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then the killer could go to Room B,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.36,0:14:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,say that the call was cut off because of the tunnel, and ask to continue the conversation in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.49,0:14:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what were the killer and Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.95,0:14:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably about the deduction quiz that takes place aboard the Mystery Train.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.96,0:14:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer used fake cue cards to pretend that Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been picked as the victim, themselves as the murderer,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.00,0:14:58.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and my daughter and her friends as the accomplices.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.97,0:15:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cards said that Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} should swap rooms with my daughter to create a vanishing corpse trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.39,0:15:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} should've been booked into Room B in the first-class car,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.11,0:15:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the fake cue cards were just an emergency measure
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.32,0:15:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and as a precaution, he picked the children to be the detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.45,0:15:29.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, even if detectives arrived at Carriage 7, Room B, my daughter and her friends would delay them as part of their role as accomplices.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.00,0:15:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the plot quickly fell through, and my daughter and the kids ended up coming back to Room B in this carriage, where the crime took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.05,0:15:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.13,0:15:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understood how the killer moved Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to Room B,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.55,0:15:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but when did they come out of the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.97,0:15:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.97,0:15:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer quickly murdered Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and then left immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.77,0:15:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the conductor in front of Room A would've seen something!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.60,0:16:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he didn't, which means the most suspicious person is whoever the conductor saw peering past a door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What door was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.11,0:16:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door at the other end of the corridor from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.41,0:16:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when I was in front of Room E, so I think it was Noto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s Room A.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.16,0:16:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.17,0:16:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't say something like that without any proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.08,0:16:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know exactly who you saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.05,0:16:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.21,0:16:21.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Conductor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.76,0:16:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the suspicious figure? The killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.18,0:16:28.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you saw was yourself in front of Room E...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.81,0:16:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...in a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.98,0:16:40.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.19,0:16:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer covered the inner side of their door with a mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.03,0:16:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and when the conductor was in front of Idenami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s Room E,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.12,0:16:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they opened their door so they wouldn't be seen leaving Room B.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.71,0:16:58.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if the killer was in Room B at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.67,0:17:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then how would they open the door to their own room?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.42,0:17:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer attached fishing line to the doorknob and passed it through the handrail by the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.05,0:17:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They took it into Room B, waited for a good time, and then pulled on it to open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.43,0:17:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.94,0:17:18.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This trick would be obvious if the position of the mirror was too close or too far from the other side of the carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.82,0:17:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it had to be the passenger in\NRoom C, in the middle of rooms A-B-C-D-E.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.28,0:17:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Andō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it could only be you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.04,0:17:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.08,0:17:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't reach Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, Dad or even Sera{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.63,0:17:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.01,0:17:47.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go check out the first-class car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.26,0:17:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.60,0:17:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They seem to be in the middle of a deduction show right now, so we probably shouldn't disturb them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.90,0:18:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mirror?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.90,0:18:08.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How on Earth could I bring a mirror large enough to cover a whole door into the train?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.03,0:18:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The painting you said you were asked to analyse...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.70,0:18:17.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you placed about three slides of\Nmirrored glass between the canvases,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.58,0:18:19.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you would have enough mirror to cover the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.59,0:18:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That painting was quite heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.34,0:18:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's because the forgery's made of solid gold...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.84,0:18:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's wood, covered in gold leaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.60,0:18:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the painting that's heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.10,0:18:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And inside, just like {\i1}Sensei{\i0} said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.77,0:18:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...there's three mirror pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And seeing that one of them has a spot of paint in the same color as the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.78,0:18:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you must've prepared it so that the conductor wouldn't realize he was looking at a reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.61,0:18:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'd left it as it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.91,0:18:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Room E's label would've been reflected too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.29,0:18:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Andō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.00,0:19:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you explain those three mirror pieces?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.96,0:19:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And please don't try to say
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.38,0:19:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that they were put in before you were tasked with analyzing it, and you never noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.18,0:19:16.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can just ask the client who commissioned you to analyze it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.48,0:19:21.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Assuming that such a person even exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.91,0:19:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, isn't that going a bit far?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.79,0:19:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was my favourite, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.84,0:19:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one-piece in that suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.89,0:19:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it about time you stopped doing this kind of thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.73,0:20:01.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sharon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.82,0:20:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.49,0:20:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think that kid would get his mother involved in our feud.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.37,0:20:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put myself up for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.37,0:20:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told him that if the opponent was a star of the silver screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.58,0:20:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then he better cast me, the legendary Japanese actress, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.25,0:20:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm a bit disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.25,0:20:32.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I always thought you might someday teach me what\Nmakeup you used to keep your aging face so radiant...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.84,0:20:37.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think that the great actress Sharon Vineyard was nothing but some aging makeup!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.51,0:20:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's actually pretty hard, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.56,0:20:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pretending that you're older than you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.48,0:20:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what you said back when we crossed paths in the passageway...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.15,0:20:53.82,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If we outwit you again, then this time, will you give up on her for good?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.36,0:20:56.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.45,0:20:58.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly what it says on the tin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.91,0:21:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because according to Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s one of us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.37,0:21:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.54,0:21:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you really think you can beat us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.05,0:21:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you know? Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s team is actually a step ahead of you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.92,0:21:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.59,0:21:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already took that Sera girl you left sleeping in your room back to her own room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.85,0:21:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You work quickly, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.19,0:21:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's strange... The boy's still going through his deduction show.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.23,0:21:32.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have somebody else helping you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.90,0:21:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.53,0:21:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might have a special guest on our team!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.72,0:22:00.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shū...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.10,0:22:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shū{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-nii{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.92,0:23:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your chances of winning...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.96,0:23:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...are huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.63,0:23:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} got a hold of your weak point, Sharon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.72,0:23:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.68,0:23:54.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.10,0:23:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't find Haibara anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.23,0:24:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.44,0:24:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: The Jet-Black Mystery Train (Destination)!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.53,0:24:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: The Ultimate Cast!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.45,0:24:20.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Gin!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.04,0:24:20.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Vodka!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.71,0:24:21.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Bourbon!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.25,0:24:21.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.71,0:24:23.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's the order that old man Mouri drank alcohol in!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.54,0:24:24.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What.
